Old female left valley one day and came back with arms full of shoots and roots. When Ostman fled she started to come after him, but stopped when he fired a shot in the air.

The young male showed great interest in Ostman, used a dipper Ostman made from a tin can, played by holding his feet in his hands and bouncing on his bottom, drank out of the palm of his hand, had heavy pads on feet, could climb cliffs with just footing for big toe.

Young female and young male chased each other and played the bouncing game. All of them sat down by bending their knees outward and going straight down, and came straight up without using their hands. The young female carried to the older creatures roots the young male threw from the cliff.
Creatures were wrestling, apparently in play. Continued for all the time observers were there.
Pile of fecal matter found covered with moss stripped off a rock face

Forearm longer than a man's, and could break a stick by wrenching or twisting it in a way no man could. Became attached to keeper. Usually silent, except occasional half bark, half growl. Drank milk. Exact height 4'7'', weight 127 lbs.
Hair colour described as reddish brown in one story, black in another. Black is chosen because that story appears to be directly quoting the informant. Source of the other story is not clear.

David Churchill identifies this creature as a female, Dennis Taylor does not. Churchill apparently was closer. When first seen it was sitting with its hands between its knees.

Did not appear to use its thumbs. Made blowing noises fluttering upper lip, seemed to be in reply to grunts from female. Had no hair in armpit, and hair at point of shoulder divided in every direction, leaving a slightly bare spot.
Kneeling at first, stood up when eating, carried baby across her lap. Tore nest apart and let baby take first rodent but did not hand it to him. She and the male each made their own stacks of rocks.
Held onto mother's hair all it could, looked at her, didn't look around, seemed to try to keep out of the male's reach.
Breasts lower on body than human's. Didn't use thumbs in picking leaves.

Head rested on hand, elbow rested on knee as it watched divers for half an hour. Smell and sound (whistling calls) are from other occasions, not this particular incident.

Two possible footprint impressions in soft gravel measured 19 inches. When creature hit by flashlight smell intensified, like ammonia or sulphur, went back to normal after. No explanation on form of how incident ended.

Things the creature may have done included trying to push the car off the road, trying to smash its way into the car, and trying to pick up the back of the car or at least hold it back. It once thrust its face right up to the witness' face, but backed off when he threatened to punch it, and did not come as close again.
Creature was looking at dogs when first seen. It bumped into a person, and it apparently held a door from closing. It left a hand print.
Creature apparently tipped over a trailer load of culverts.
There were scratches left on the car. He had left a cantalope rind outside the car (and had more inside). Didn't notice if the rind was gone in the morning.
Big police dog wouldn't chase it.
Hands touched ground making fast turns. Hand print was in dust on car. Sound was a mumble.

One arm was swinging, the other apparently held bent in front of body.
Creature reached in car window and struck or grabbed observer's arm, scratching it when she drove off. (Obviously wasn't trying to hang on) It smelled terrible, like a dead animal.

Tracks near blue huckleberry patch where both berries and leaves stripped. Camper trucks with people in them shaken in the middle of the night.

Eyes said to be blue-glowing, although it was seen in daylight.

Goat and dog reported frightened. Creature said to have tried to break into trailer.

Dogs barked and ran after creature, but soon returned and subsequently would not leave the porch at night. Creature ran with its arms held over its head.

c_decribe_unusual: Although she turned and looked at his skiff the sasquatch did not appear to realize there was someone in it--certainly showed no awareness that she was looking down the barrel of a rifle. Some specific descriptions the questions do not cover: Blackskin on fingers; head shape pongid; foot had no arch but was very flexible. When she knelt on one knee, lifting that heel, her foot bent in a 'C' shape; eyes were beautiful, like a doe's eyes; fur in really good condition; long hair on head and shoulders covered ears and flowed down back like a mane; rose straight up from squat without using hands; waddled side to side, but no up and down motion, 'really fluid'; abdomen extremely swollen, one great arc from sternum to pubis, obviously late term pregnancy; breasts visible but not flacid, size and form comparable to human; less hair on face, palms, soles and midline of thorax and on some parts of chest. Weight estimate at least 600 lbs., maybe a whole lot more.
